title: "Front Open Space" means the space between the boundary line of a plot abutting the means of access/road/street and the building line
clause_text: "Front Open Space" means the space between the boundary line of a plot abutting the means of access/road/street and the building line. Plots facing two or more means of accesses/roads/streets shall be deemed to front on all such means of accesses/roads/streets.
